The new environmental review ordered by the State Department may delay a decision until 2013, after the elections next year, even though officials deny that politicians were involved in the decision.
Obama said last week in a written statement that the decision was a task of the State Department and promised his support.
The 1700-mile pipeline became a link between Canada and the Gulf of Mexico.
It would pump 700,000 barrels of oil a day from the province of Alberta to the refineries in Texas.
