Climate change has slowed the economy
In the first year in which Mario L<0xC3><0xB3>pez Valdez is in the government, unemployment and black labour rose in Sinaloa, while foreign investment declined and the economy stagnated.
2011 will be remembered in Sinaloa’s economic history. It is the first year in which Mario L<0xC3><0xB3>pez Valdez, who calls himself the initiator of change and fuelled great hopes for economic growth, is in the government. However, due to climatic adversities, growth cannot be talked about, but on the contrary, the main economic indicators deteriorated.
