According to a report published by the Consejo Mexicano para el Desarrollo Rural Sustentable (Mexican Council for Sustainable Agricultural Development), 582,000 hectares of agricultural land have been damaged, of which 78.03 percent have been completely destroyed and the remaining 21.07 percent have been partially destroyed.
