Modol, like Rold<0xC3><0xA1>n and Bayona with urban development experience, considers the proposal to be an "intellectual challenge" that carries "some dangers".
Dangers as a result of the "uncertainty that the design of a public space today entails" according to the experiences from the 1980s, which had their "swan song" in the area of the forum.
The first fear is one’s own limitation on what may be built.
