It is the whole of Europe that is humiliated at the international level.
We are concerned about transfers of sovereignty towards Europe, and it is the whole of Europe that is gradually losing its sovereignty, and thus every single one of the nations that are affiliated to it.
The urgency is to restore the leadership of the European project to the people's sovereignty.
Because it is up to the whole Europeans to reduce the burden of their debts, to free themselves from the markets and to initiate a future through investment.
The exit from the crisis is conditional on decisions at European level, which cannot be made without total democratic legitimacy, without certainly leading us to destruction.
After this proposal by Jacques Delors and the Socialists has been fought over for a long time, today everyone is pushing European economic management to do so.
I agree.
